question: Killers of the Flower Moon vs. Taylor Swift
description:
This is a market on whether 'Killers of the Flower Moon' (2023) or 'Taylor Swift: The Eras Tour' (2023) has a higher weekend gross on Oct 20 - 22 weekend. The respective "Domestic Weekend" tabs on https://www.boxofficemojo.com/title/tt5537002/ and https://www.boxofficemojo.com/release/rl4054352641/ will be used to resolve this market once the values for the 3-day weekend (October 20-22) are final (i.e. not studio estimates).

This market will resolve to "Killers" if the 3-day domestic gross of 'Killers of the Flower Moon' is greater than 'Taylor Swift: The Eras Tour'. This market will resolve to "Taylor Swift" if the 3-day domestic gross of 'Taylor Swift: The Eras Tour' is greater than 'Killers of the Flower Moon'. If the domestic grosses are exactly the same the market will resolve to 50-50.

Please note, this market will resolve according to the Box Office Mojo numbers under Domestic Weekend for the 3-day weekend (which typically includes Thursday's previews), regardless of whether domestic refers to only the USA, or to USA and Canada, etc. 

If there is no final data available by October 30, 2023, 11:59:59 PM ET, another credible resolution source will be chosen.

question: Will Argentina presidential election go to a second round?
description:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if the 2023 Argentina presidential election requires a second round of voting. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from Argentina's government (e.g. https://www.argentina.gob.ar/elecciones-2023), however a consensus of credible reporting will also suffice.

question: Will any New York Times staff face consequences for the Gaza hospital strike headline?
description: This market will resolve to "Yes" if any New York Times journalist or executive faces formal consequences as a direct result of the incorrect 'Israel strikes Gaza hospital' headline. Formal consequences may include, but are not limited to, termination, suspension or disciplinary action. Informal consequences such as negative publicity will not be considered. The market will resolve to "No" if no such action is taken by November 1, 2023, 11:59 PM ET. Official announcements from The New York Times or confirmed reports from reputable news sources will be used to determine the resolution.

question: Will the New York Times definitively state Israel was not behind the Gaza hospital blast?
description: This market will resolve to "Yes" if The New York Times, on any of its official platforms, definitively states that Israel was not responsible for the hospital blast in Gaza. This could be in the form of a corrected article, a retraction, an updated headline, or a public statement explicitly attributing the blast to a different party (Hamas, PIJ, etc.). If The New York Times does not make such a definitive statement by November 1, 2023, the market will resolve to "No". Official New York Times publications and statements will be used to determine the resolution.

question: Will a Korean team win LOL Worlds 2023?
description:

Korean teams are as follows: Gen.G, T1, KT Rolster, Dplus KIA
